{% extends "www/_layouts/layout-fullwidth.njk" %}
{% set pageTitle="Style guide" %}
{% set section = "Styles" %}
{# Imports #}
{%- from "wmnds/components/content-tiles/normal/_normal.njk" import wmndsContentTilesNormal -%}
{% from "wmnds/components/link/link/_link.njk" import wmndsLink %}
{% from "wmnds/components/inset-text/_inset-text.njk" import wmndsInsetText %}
{# Set array of tiles #}

{% block content %}
{# About the style guide #}
<div class="wmnds-grid">
  <div class="wmnds-col-1 wmnds-col-md-3-4">
      <h2>Writing content for West Midlands Network</h2>
    <p>You should create all content with user-focused content design principles. This means content has an identified user need and is written in plain English.</p>
    <p>Read the
        {{
            wmndsLink({
                link: "https://www.gov.uk/guidance/content-design/what-is-content-design",
                linkTitle: "GOV.UK introduction to content design",
                text: "GOV.UK introduction to content design"
            })
        }}
        to find out more.</p>
    <p>If something is not covered by this style guide, check the 
        {{
            wmndsLink({
                link: "https://www.gov.uk/guidance/style-guide/a-to-z-of-gov-uk-style",
                linkTitle: "GOV.UK Style Guide",
                text: "GOV.UK style guide"
            })
        }}
    . You can also email Samresha Purewal if you think something is missing from this guidance.</p>
    {{
        wmndsInsetText({
            thinner: true,
            html: "If you’re talking about day-to-day services (bus, train or tram), you may need to make it clear that West Midlands Network does not run these.<br /><br />For example, you could say: \“We don’t run the buses, trains or trams. We can point you in the right direction if you need help.\""
        })
    }}
    <br />
    <br />
    <h3>A to Z of style</h3>
    <p>JSON data is in here, organised by letter in accordion. The user should have the option to expand all and collapse all.</p>
  </div>
</div>
<br />
{% endblock %}